WEBVTT

00:05.072 --> 00:06.006 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff.

00:06.039 --> 00:07.841 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:07.875 --> 00:10.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the
"NewsHour"s tonight:
Front-runners Donald Trump and
Hillary Clinton

00:10.777 --> 00:17.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
win big in yesterday's
delegate-rich primaries,
pushing the two closer to their
party's nomination

00:17.084 --> 00:20.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- what this means for the rest
of the candidates
in the race.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Also ahead
this Wednesday:

00:22.222 --> 00:26.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
We will always save lives, and
indeed humanity

00:26.693 --> 00:32.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
itself. But to play that role,
we must make
America strong again.

00:32.933 --> 00:36.904 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In an
issue-focused moment
of Donald Trump's campaign, the
self-presumed

00:36.937 --> 00:42.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
eventual nominee makes a crucial
foreign policy
speech, outlining his views on
the United

00:42.242 --> 00:44.011 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
States' role in the world.

00:44.044 --> 00:49.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a writer
follows the case
of a grisly rape and murder to
find out if

00:49.182 --> 00:50.984 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it could have been avoided.

00:51.018 --> 00:56.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELI SANDERS, Author, "While the
City Slept":
You can see how relatively
little potentially

00:56.957 --> 01:04.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it might have cost to steer him
or forcefully
nudge him in a different
direction much earlier

01:04.064 --> 01:05.399 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on.

01:05.432 --> 01:11.872 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All that and
more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:11.905 --> 01:14.708 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:14.741 --> 01:24.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Today brought a
sizable shift
in the presidential race. The
Republican front-runner

01:25.018 --> 01:30.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
turned his attention from his
rivals to his
world view. But one of those
rivals rolled

01:30.490 --> 01:32.092 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out a running mate.

01:32.125 --> 01:34.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
John Yang reports on this
campaign day.

01:34.227 --> 01:37.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
It's time to shake the rust off
America's

01:37.431 --> 01:43.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
foreign policy. It's time to
invite new voices
and new visions into the fold.

01:43.804 --> 01:48.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Donald Trump, fresh
from a decisive
sweep of Tuesday's primaries,
delivered his

01:48.575 --> 01:51.812 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
first major speech on foreign
policy.

01:51.845 --> 01:53.847 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SEN. TED CRUZ (R-TX),
Presidential Candidate:
Carly Fiorina!

01:53.880 --> 01:58.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Ted Cruz answered
with a headline
of his own, naming former rival
Carly Fiorina

01:58.418 --> 02:00.253 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as his running mate.

02:00.287 --> 02:06.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. TED CRUZ: This ticket is
about the future.
It is about our children. It is
about our

02:06.560 --> 02:12.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
grandchildren. The stakes of
this election,
we are not simply wagering on a
sporting contest.

02:12.499 --> 02:15.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CARLY FIORINA (R), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
This is a fight worth having.
This is a fight

02:15.602 --> 02:20.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
worth winning. And with your
help, we will
win this fight!

02:20.173 --> 02:25.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Cruz is banking on
next week's
Indiana primary to give him new
life. Trump

02:25.912 --> 02:31.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now has more than three-quarters
of the delegates
he needs for a first-ballot
victory. Last

02:31.752 --> 02:36.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
night, he declared himself the
presumptive
nominee, and took aim at the
Democrats' likely

02:36.623 --> 02:38.492 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
standard-bearer, Hillary
Clinton.

02:38.525 --> 02:42.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Well, I think the
only card
she has is the woman's card. She
has nothing

02:42.129 --> 02:46.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
else going for her. And,
frankly, if Hillary
Clinton were a man, I don't
think she would

02:46.900 --> 02:48.602 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
get 5 percent of the vote.

02:48.635 --> 02:54.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Clinton answered the
jibe after
winning four states, putting her
90 percent

02:54.174 --> 02:56.076 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the way to clinching the
nomination.

02:56.109 --> 02:59.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate:
Well, if fighting for women's
health care

02:59.079 --> 03:06.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and paid family leave and equal
pay is playing
the woman card, then deal me in!

03:06.453 --> 03:08.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

03:08.188 --> 03:13.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: But Bernie Sanders is
not ready
to throw in his hand. The
Vermont senator

03:13.226 --> 03:15.162 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
spoke today in West Lafayette,
Indiana.

03:15.195 --> 03:23.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. BERNIE SANDERS (VT-I),
Presidential Candidate:
We are in this campaign to win
and to become

03:23.403 --> 03:23.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Democratic nominee.

03:23.970 --> 03:25.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

03:25.772 --> 03:27.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: At the same time,
Sanders told
The New York Times he plans to
lay off hundreds

03:27.541 --> 03:31.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of campaign workers and focus on
winning California.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.980 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang.

03:34.014 --> 03:38.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will examine
the race, and
hear more of Donald Trump's
foreign policy

03:38.051 --> 03:39.986 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
speech, after the news summary.

03:40.020 --> 03:44.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In the day's
other news:
The U.S. Supreme Court lent a
seemingly sympathetic

03:44.157 --> 03:48.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ear to former Virginia Governor
Bob McDonnell.
He faces two years in prison for
accepting

03:48.562 --> 03:53.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
thousands of dollars in gifts
and loans from
a businessman. But in today's
arguments, both

03:53.066 --> 03:58.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
liberal and conservative
justices suggested
the federal bribery law is
overbroad. A decision

03:58.238 --> 04:00.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
could come in June.

04:00.040 --> 04:04.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Former House
Speaker Dennis
Hastert was sentenced today to
15 months in

04:04.211 --> 04:10.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
federal prison for paying hush
money to cover
up sexual abuse. The Illinois
Republican admitted

04:10.417 --> 04:15.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that he abused at least one
teenager as a
wrestling coach in high school.
He told a

04:15.455 --> 04:19.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
federal court in Chicago: "What
I did was
wrong and I regret it."

04:19.993 --> 04:24.097 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will hear about Hastert's day
in court
later in the program.

04:24.131 --> 04:30.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The fight over
federal funding
to control the Zika virus will
likely go unresolved

04:31.004 --> 04:36.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
before next week's congressional
recess. The
White House asked for $1.9
billion back in

04:36.843 --> 04:42.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
February. But House Speaker Paul
Ryan suggested
today that may be more than
necessary.

04:42.315 --> 04:45.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House:
The administration has a bit of
a track record

04:45.685 --> 04:50.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of over-requesting what they
need. So we will
sit down with the appropriators
to figure

04:50.090 --> 04:53.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out the best way forward, to
make sure that
we're good stewards of the
taxpayers' money

04:53.693 --> 04:57.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and to make sure that we have
what we need
to combat and stay ahead of the
Zika virus

04:57.297 --> 04:59.032 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
issue.

04:59.065 --> 05:00.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: At the White
House, Press
Secretary Josh Earnest fired
back, saying

05:00.901 --> 05:02.736 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the delay is putting the country
at risk.

05:02.769 --> 05:06.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSH EARNEST, White House Press
Secretary:
You had the director of the
National Institutes

05:06.373 --> 05:11.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of Health and a high-ranking
official from
the Centers for Disease Control
stand at this

05:11.411 --> 05:16.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
podium about three weeks ago and
say they
didn't have the resources that
they needed

05:16.850 --> 05:22.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that should be used to fully
prepare for the
onset of the Zika virus.

05:22.322 --> 05:25.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Zika has been
linked to
a rare birth defect, and is
spreading rapidly

05:25.392 --> 05:27.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
through the Americas.

05:27.127 --> 05:31.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For a second day,
a severe
weather system menaced a large
swathe of the

05:31.131 --> 05:35.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nation. The threat of tornadoes
waned, but
Kansas City suffered significant
flooding

05:35.936 --> 05:41.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
early today. And winds of 60
miles an hour
tore through the greater Houston
area, blowing

05:41.508 --> 05:46.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
trees onto houses. So far, one
death is blamed
on the storms.

05:46.146 --> 05:50.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In the Middle
East, Israeli
security forces killed a
Palestinian woman

05:50.150 --> 05:55.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and her teenage brother, the
latest in a wave
of violent incidents. It
happened at a security

05:55.322 --> 05:59.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
checkpoint between the West Bank
and Jerusalem.
Police said they fired after the
woman pulled

06:00.026 --> 06:04.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a knife on an officer. They said
they found
knives on the boy's body as
well.

06:04.598 --> 06:09.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The only
surviving suspect
in November's terrorist attacks
in Paris was

06:09.603 --> 06:15.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
extradited to France today.
Salah Abdeslam
is the alleged logistical
planner of the assault

06:16.009 --> 06:21.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that left 130 people dead. He
was taken to
a Paris court after an
early-morning transfer

06:21.982 --> 06:25.785 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from Brussels, and his lawyer
said he plans
to cooperate.

06:25.819 --> 06:29.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANK BERTON, Attorney for Salah
Abdeslam
(through translator): He gave a
spontaneous

06:29.356 --> 06:33.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
statement to the investigating
judge, and
he insisted he would explain
himself later.

06:33.660 --> 06:37.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The judge put him under formal
investigation
on charges of murder, complicity
of murder

06:37.931 --> 06:42.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with a terrorist organization,
holding weapons
and explosives, and kidnapping.

06:42.702 --> 06:46.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Abdeslam was
captured in Brussels
last month.

06:46.673 --> 06:50.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Back in this
country, it's
being called the biggest gang
crackdown ever

06:50.277 --> 06:55.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in New York City. In pre-dawn
raids, federal
agents and police arrested
scores of suspects.

06:55.515 --> 07:01.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said two rival gangs have
terrorized
housing projects in the Bronx.
In all, 120

07:01.721 --> 07:03.423 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
people are being charged.

07:03.456 --> 07:07.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The latest
nation's report
card shows high school seniors
are losing

07:07.460 --> 07:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ground. The U.S. Department of
Education reports
that average math scores dropped
last year

07:13.199 --> 07:19.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
for the first time since
assessments began
in 1992. Reading scores were
flat, but they

07:19.439 --> 07:25.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have dropped five points since
1992. As a
result, only 37 percent of all
seniors were

07:25.545 --> 07:28.081 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
judged college-ready in math and
reading.

07:28.114 --> 07:31.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The Federal
Reserve today
left short-term interest rates
unchanged for

07:32.018 --> 07:36.690 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
now. In a statement,
policy-makers said there's
been solid job growth, but
economic activity

07:36.723 --> 07:41.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
appears to be slowing. As a
result, the Fed
decided to hold off on a further
hike until

07:41.628 --> 07:43.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
June at the earliest.

07:43.496 --> 07:47.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Wall Street took
the Fed's
news in stride. The Dow Jones
industrial average

07:47.434 --> 07:56.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
gained 51 points to close at
18041. The Nasdaq
fell 25 points, as Apple slumped
6 percent,

07:56.609 --> 07:58.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and the S&amp;P 500 added three.

07:58.878 --> 08:03.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Still to come
on the "NewsHour":
is it game over for Ted Cruz and
John Kasich?;

08:03.750 --> 08:09.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump calls for a hard
line on negotiations
abroad; former House Speaker
Dennis Hastert

08:09.322 --> 08:23.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sentenced in a hush money
scandal; and much
more.

08:23.570 --> 08:28.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: To dig into last
night's election
results and discuss the race's
dramatic shift

08:28.074 --> 08:33.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going into the last leg of the
primary contest,
we are joined once again by
Susan Page of

08:33.813 --> 08:37.951 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
USA Today and Reid Wilson of the
Morning Consult.

08:37.984 --> 08:39.652 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And welcome back to both of you.

08:39.686 --> 08:41.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Big night last night.

08:41.488 --> 08:45.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Reid, how did the results last
night change
the trajectory of this race? And
let's start

08:45.558 --> 08:47.394 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with the Republicans.

08:47.427 --> 08:49.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REID WILSON, Morning Consult: On
the Republican
side, Donald Trump swept just
about everything

08:49.329 --> 08:53.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he possibly could have. The only
place where
John Kasich or Ted Cruz picked
up any delegates

08:53.967 --> 08:57.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
