big wins earlier
this month.

09:19.092 --> 09:24.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem for Trump, though,
is that coming
up in May, he's still about 250
delegates

09:24.164 --> 09:29.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
short of the number he needs.
But in the five
contests in May, there are only
199 delegates

09:29.469 --> 09:33.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
available. So if Ted Cruz and
John Kasich
want to stick around, they sure
can, least

09:33.706 --> 09:35.175 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
until June.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Susan, where
does this
leave Ted Cruz and John Kasich?

09:37.777 --> 09:40.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE, Washington Bureau
Chief, USA Today:
Well, I think that leaves them
in a predicament,

09:40.713 --> 09:45.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because Donald Trump is now --
he called himself
last not the presumptive
nominee. Now, maybe

09:45.552 --> 09:48.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we're just a step short of that,
but he is
certainly now the likely
nominee.

09:48.488 --> 09:52.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is now likely to be able to
get a majority
of convention delegates on that
first ballot

09:53.026 --> 09:58.064 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
or come so close, it is
impossible politically
to deny him the nomination. And
you saw him

09:58.097 --> 10:01.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reflect that today by giving a
big speech
on foreign policy that we had
never heard

10:01.634 --> 10:03.403 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
before.

10:03.436 --> 10:06.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You also saw Ted Cruz trying to
get back in
the story by doing something
that seemed a

10:06.372 --> 10:09.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
little premature, which was
announcing his
vice presidential pick.

